ibmWanRestoralTable.name: ibmWanRestoralTable
ibmWanRestoralTable.description: A list of WAN Restoral table entries. The number of entries should equal the current number of primary link for WAN Restoral. The table has a row for primary link. Each row has information about the current status of that link.

ibmWanRestoralEntry.name: ibmWanRestoralEntry
ibmWanRestoralEntry.description: A WAN Restoral table entry describing current status of the primary link. The table has a row for each primary link. Rows in this table can not be created or deleted via SNMP commands

ibmwrsPriNetifIndex.name: ibmwrsPriNetifIndex
ibmwrsPriNetifIndex.description: The interface index of the primary net interface. This is the same as mib-2 ifIndex for that interface.

ibmwrsSecNetifIndex.name: ibmwrsSecNetifIndex
ibmwrsSecNetifIndex.description: The interface index of the secondary net interface. This is the same as mib-2 ifIndex for that interface.

ibmwrsEnabled.name: ibmwrsEnabled
ibmwrsEnabled.description: The flag indicates that restoral of this primary interface is currently enabled.

ibmwrsActive.name: ibmwrsActive
ibmwrsActive.description: The flag indicates that restoral of this primary interface is currently active.

ibmwrsDuration.name: ibmwrsDuration
ibmwrsDuration.description: The value in 1/100s of a second indicating the current or most recent duration that the secondary net interface was up. The value is current if ibmwrsActive has a value of yes(1), otherwise it is the most recent restoral duration. If restoral has never been active, the value is 0

ibmwrsAttempts.name: ibmwrsAttempts
ibmwrsAttempts.description: The number of times an attempt was made to restore the primary.

ibmwrsActuals.name: ibmwrsActuals
ibmwrsActuals.description: The number of times the primary was actually restored by the secondary.

ibmwrsFwdPkts.name: ibmwrsFwdPkts
ibmwrsFwdPkts.description: The number of packets forwarded during the current or most recent restoral.

ibmWanRerouteTable.name: ibmWanRerouteTable
ibmWanRerouteTable.description: A list of WAN Reroute table entries. The number of entries should equal the current number of primary link for WAN Reroute. The table has a row for primary link. Each row has information about the current status of that link.

ibmWanRerouteEntry.name: ibmWanRerouteEntry
ibmWanRerouteEntry.description: A WAN Reroute table entry describing current status of the primary link. The table has a row for each primary link. Rows in this table can not be created or deleted via SNMP commands

ibmwrrPriNetifIndex.name: ibmwrrPriNetifIndex
ibmwrrPriNetifIndex.description: The interface index of the primary net interface. This is the same as mib-2 ifIndex for that interface.

ibmwrrAltNetifIndex.name: ibmwrrAltNetifIndex
ibmwrrAltNetifIndex.description: The interface index of the alternate net interface. This is the same as mib-2 ifIndex for that interface.

ibmwrrEnabled.name: ibmwrrEnabled
ibmwrrEnabled.description: The flag indicates that reroute of this primary interface is currently enabled.

ibmwrrActive.name: ibmwrrActive
ibmwrrActive.description: The flag indicates that reroute of this primary interface is currently active.

ibmwrrDuration.name: ibmwrrDuration
ibmwrrDuration.description: The value in 1/100s of a second indicating the current or most recent duration that the alternate net interface was up. The value is current if ibmwrrActive has a value of yes(1), otherwise it is the most recent reroute duration. If reroute has never been active, the value is 0

ibmwrrAttempts.name: ibmwrrAttempts
ibmwrrAttempts.description: The number of times an attempt was made to reroute the primary.

ibmwrrActuals.name: ibmwrrActuals
ibmwrrActuals.description: The number of times the primary was actually rerouted by the secondary.

ibmwrrOverflowEnabled.name: ibmwrrOverflowEnabled
ibmwrrOverflowEnabled.description: The flag indicates that dial on overflow of this primary interface is currently enabled.

ibmwrrOverflowActive.name: ibmwrrOverflowActive
ibmwrrOverflowActive.description: The flag indicates that dial on overflow of this primary interface is currently active.

ibmwrrOverflowDuration.name: ibmwrrOverflowDuration
ibmwrrOverflowDuration.description: The value in 1/100s of a second indicating the current or most recent dial on overflow duration that the alternate net interface was up. The value is current if ibmwrrOverflowActive has a value of yes(1), otherwise it is the most recent dial on overflow duration. If dial on overflow has never been active, the value is 0

ibmwrrOverflowAttempts.name: ibmwrrOverflowAttempts
ibmwrrOverflowAttempts.description: The number of times an attempt was made to use the alternate link after the primary threshhold was reached.

ibmwrrOverflowActuals.name: ibmwrrOverflowActuals
ibmwrrOverflowActuals.description: The number of times the alternate link was actually used for overflow traffic once the primary threshhold was reached.
